summary: Here's a tip if you're having anxiety attacks. Usually when I'm having anxiety attacks, I feel numb, I'm shaking so bad to the...
body:
Music vs Anxiety

Here’s a tip if you’re having anxiety attacks. Usually when I’m having anxiety attacks, I feel numb, I’m shaking so bad to the point I can’t breathe, and everything is running around your head like all the problems in the world is flashing inside your head and you’re watching it on a slideshow. All those worst case scenarios you can think of and played on repeat. So, the first thing I do is take a deep breath, calm myself, get my phone, my headset, and go for a walk with just music. Music really helps ease my mind and forget about anxiety. Sometimes I would go to a karaoke/videoke room and sing my heart out. It was nice to be with the people you love but sometimes or most of the times you just wanted to be alone when having anxiety. But if you felt you’re so alone and just want to disappear, please don’t hesitate to reach out to your family and friends. So, what music to listen to when having anxiety? Those empowering songs you know or in your list would really help. The best for me was Taylor Swift’s old songs. Especially her song “Change”. Whenever I hear that song, I can feel that I can beat my anxiety and all the positivity will go back in my head. Having anxiety sucks and it won’t go away easily but you’ll have to hold on, listen to an uplifting music, sing your heart out, and know you’ll make it. Have a great day you amazing thing!
